thread.title: Dollar Falls to Lowest Level In More Than Three Years

author: Ira Iosebashvili
title: Dollar Falls to Lowest Level In More Than Three Years
text:
The dollar fell to its lowest level in more than three years Thursday, as strong economic data from overseas drew investors into the euro.
The Wall Street Journal Dollar Index, which measures the U.S. currency against a basket of 16 others, was down 0.3% at 82.97, its lowest level since December 2014.
